  • Method Details

    • getByAddress

      public static java.net.Inet4Address getByAddress​(byte[] addr) throws java.net.UnknownHostException, InetFactory.Inet6NotSupportedException
      Creates a Ipv4 address from bytes.
      Parameters:
      addr - An array of bytes length 4
      Returns:
      bytes as an Ipv4 address
      Throws:
      InetFactory.Inet6NotSupportedException - If the addr would translate to a valid Ipv6 address as this is not supported by Spinnaker
      java.net.UnknownHostException - if IP address is of illegal length

    • getByName

      public static java.net.Inet4Address getByName​(java.lang.String host) throws java.net.UnknownHostException, InetFactory.Inet6NotSupportedException
      Creates a Ipv4 address from String.
      Parameters:
      host - the specified hos
      Returns:
      host as an Ipv4 address
      Throws:
      InetFactory.Inet6NotSupportedException - If the host would translate to a valid Ipv6 address as this is not supported by Spinnaker
      java.net.UnknownHostException - if no IP address for the host could be found, or if a scope_id was specified for a global IPv6 address.
